				<baseName xml:lang="en">Fire proof bricks</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">防火砖</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Refractory bricks; Fireclay brick; Acidic Fire brick; Acid resistant brick</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Refractory bricks; Fireclay brick; Acidic Fire brick; Acid resistant brick</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Materials production</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Inorganic chemicals</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Fire bricks, also known as refractory bricks, withstand high heat and are great for fire pits, pizza ovens or as a liner for wood-burning stoves. They come in a variety of colors and are used especially to resist acidic actions of chemicals or weather. Fire bricks are considered to be a fire-resistant material and may keep flames away from the stud cavity and interior of walls. They are built primarily to withstand high temperature, but will also usually have a low thermal conductivity for greater energy efficiency.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">耐火砖又称耐火砖，可承受高热，是火坑、比萨炉或烧木柴炉衬的理想材料。耐火砖有多种颜色，特别适用于抵御酸性化学物质或天气的侵蚀。耐火砖被认为是一种耐火材料，可以使火焰远离墙骨空腔和墙壁内部。它们主要用于耐高温，但通常也具有较低的导热性，以提高能源效率。</common:generalComment>
